The paper discusses the queuing model for the Tactile Internet in the context of the next generation wireless networks, which involves the integration of cloud computing and radio access network (RAN) architecture. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves resource allocation and optimization problems, which are related to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of power domain non-orthogonal multiple access (PD-NOMA) technology and comparison with orthogonal frequency division multiple access (OFDM) suggests the involvement of cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.AR (Augmented Reality).
